Aim:
To write a C++ program that demonstrates the use of the this pointer inside a class.

Algorithm:
Start the program.
Create a class with data members.
Use this pointer to refer to the calling object.
Use a member function to assign values using this.
Display the result.
End the program.

Program:
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;
class Demo {
    int x;
public:
    void setData(int x) {
        this->x = x;    // using this pointer
    }

    void display() {
        cout << "Value of x: " << x << endl;
    }
};
int main() {
    Demo d;
    d.setData(100);
    d.display();
    return 0;
}

Output:
Value of x: 100

Result:
The program successfully demonstrated usage of the this pointer.
